1. Entry & Authentication Flow
•
Splash Screen (SplashActivity): The launch screen of the app.
◦
Leads to: MainActivity (Login) when the user taps "Enter App".
•
Login Screen (MainActivity): Handles user authentication.
◦
Leads to: RegisterActivity if the user needs an account.
◦
Leads to: FaceVerifyActivity if logging in as a Rescuer (Username: "Rescuer", Pwd: "123").
◦
Leads to: UserMainActivity if logging in as a regular User (Username: "User", Pwd: "123").
◦
Leads to: ErrorActivity on failed login attempts.
•
Registration (RegisterActivity): Allows new users to sign up.
◦
Leads to: FaceInputActivity if an admin code ("codeadmin") is provided (Rescuer registration).
◦
Leads to: UserMainActivity if registering as a standard user (empty admin code).
◦
Leads to: ErrorActivity if an invalid admin code is entered.
2. Rescuer Workspace (Admin/Staff)
•
Facial Verification (FaceVerifyActivity): A security layer for Rescuers.
◦
Leads to: RescuerMainActivity upon successful face match.
•
Rescuer Dashboard (RescuerMainActivity): The central hub for cat box management.
◦
Leads to: FoodStorageActivity to monitor and manage cat food levels.
◦
Leads to: CatListActivity to view the directory of cats currently in care.
◦
Leads to: HeatingActivity to control or monitor the temperature settings of the cat boxes.
•
Management Sub-pages:
◦
Cat List (CatListActivity): Displays all cats. Usually leads to CatEditActivity for updating cat profiles or medical status.
3. User Experience (Adopters/Public)
•
User Dashboard (UserMainActivity): The main interface for general users.
◦
Leads to: AdoptDetailActivity where users can view specific information about cats available for adoption.
4. Utility Pages
•
Error Page (ErrorActivity): A fallback screen shown when login fails or incorrect codes are entered.
•
Face Input (FaceInputActivity): Used during Rescuer registration to map facial data for future logins.
